# Testing Instructions

## Testing goals
- Write tests that assert behavior, not implementation trivia.
- Prefer explicit setup and assertions.
- Cover edge cases and failure paths when behavior is changed.

## Test quality
- Keep tests readable and local in intent.
- Avoid brittle mocks unless they are already the project norm.
- State what behavior each test protects.
